166typedef struct UiObject_ {
167 char fname[200]; /*< \todo document this */
168 char command[200]; /*< \todo document this */
169 bool firstRun; /*< If this UiObject has been put through the
170 user interaction processor. */
171 EmbVector controlPoints[10]; /*< Storage for however many Rubber Points the
172 design needs. */
173 char controlPointLabels[10][200]; /*< Storage for the labels for the Rubber Points
174 using the same indexing. */
175 int n_controlPoints; /*< The number of entries in the controlPoints
176 and controlPointsLabels. */
177 int numPoints; /*< The number of points if we consider the object as a Polygon. */
178 int minPoints; /*< The minimum number of points needed to make the
179 polygon look somewhat like the design. */
180 int maxPoints; /*< The maximum number of points before adding more will
181 do nothing but slow down the program. */
182 EmbVector center; /*< Where the polygon is centered. */
183 EmbVector scale; /*< The scale of the object: note that the default
184 may not be (1.0, 1.0). */
185 EmbReal rotation; /*< \todo document this */
186 uint32_t mode; /*< The mode argument records what kind of design we are
187 using and how to interact with it. */
188 char path_desc[1000]; /*< The SVG style path spec. */
189 char text[200]; /*< The text to be rendered to the scene. */
190 int textJustify; /*< One of the JUSTIFY_* constants representing what kind
191 of alignment to use. */
192 char textFont[200]; /*< The file name of the font to use. */
193 EmbReal textHeight; /*< The text height. */
194 EmbReal textRotation; /*< The rotation of the text in the scene. */
195 //GLuint texture_id; /*< Pointer to a texture that may be rendered to the object. */
196 char id[200]; /*< \todo document this */
197 int pattern_index; /*< \todo document this */
198 char type[200]; /*< \todo document this */
199 int object_index; /*< \todo document this */
200 bool selectable; /*< \todo document this */
201 EmbColor color; /*< \todo document this */
202} UiObject;

431enum OBJ_KEYS {
432OBJ_TYPE = 0, //value type - int: See OBJ_TYPE_VALUES
433OBJ_NAME = 1, //value type - str: See OBJ_NAME_VALUES
434OBJ_LAYER = 2, //value type - str: "USER", "DEFINED", "STRINGS", etc...
435OBJ_COLOR = 3, //value type - int: 0-255 //TODO: Use color chart in formats/format-dxf.h for this
436OBJ_LTYPE = 4, //value type - int: See OBJ_LTYPE_VALUES
437OBJ_LWT = 5, //value type - int: 0-27
438OBJ_RUBBER = 6 //value type - int: See OBJ_RUBBER_VALUES
439};

614static const EmbReal emb_constant_pi = 3.14159265358979323846;
615
616/*
617 * \brief Convert \a a to a QPointF.
618 */
619inline QPointF
620to_QPointF(EmbVector a)
621{
622 QPointF result(a.x, a.y);
623 return result;
624}
625
626/*
627 * \brief Convert \a a to an EmbVector.
628 */
629inline EmbVector
630to_EmbVector(QPointF a)
631{
632 EmbVector v;
633 v.x = a.x();
634 v.y = a.y();
635 return v;
636}
637
638/*
639 * \brief Wrapper for embVector_add to use the syntax \a a + \a b.
640 */
641inline EmbVector
642operator+(EmbVector a, EmbVector b)
643{
644 return embVector_add(a, b);
645}
646
647/*
648 * \brief Wrapper for embVector_subtract to use the syntax \a a - \a b.
649 */
650inline EmbVector
651operator-(EmbVector a, EmbVector b)
652{
653 return embVector_subtract(a, b);
654}
655
659inline EmbReal
660radians(EmbReal degrees)
661{
662 return (degrees*emb_constant_pi/180.0);
663}
664
668inline EmbReal
669degrees(EmbReal radian)
670{
671 return (radian*180.0/emb_constant_pi);
672}
673
677class BaseObject : public QGraphicsPathItem
678{
679public:
680 BaseObject(QGraphicsItem* parent = 0);
681 virtual ~BaseObject();
682
683 enum { Type = OBJ_TYPE_BASE };
684 virtual int type() const { return Type; }
685
686 QPen objPen;
687 QPen lwtPen;
688 QLineF objLine;
689 int objRubberMode;
690 QHash<QString, QPointF> objRubberPoints;
691 QHash<QString, QString> objRubberTexts;
692 qint64 objID;
693
694 qint64 objectID() const { return objID; }
695 QPen objectPen() const { return objPen; }
696 QColor objectColor() const { return objPen.color(); }
697 QRgb objectColorRGB() const { return objPen.color().rgb(); }
698 Qt::PenStyle objectLineType() const { return objPen.style(); }
699 EmbReal objectLineWeight() const { return lwtPen.widthF(); }
700 QPainterPath objectPath() const { return path(); }
701 int objectRubberMode() const { return objRubberMode; }
702 QPointF objectRubberPoint(const QString& key) const;
703 QString objectRubberText(const QString& key) const;
704
705 QPointF objectCenter() const { return scenePos(); }
706 EmbReal objectCenterX() const { return scenePos().x(); }
707 EmbReal objectCenterY() const { return scenePos().y(); }
708
709 void setObjectCenter(EmbVector center)
710 {
711 setPos(center.x, center.y);
712 }
713 void setObjectCenterX(EmbReal centerX) { setX(centerX); }
714 void setObjectCenterY(EmbReal centerY) { setY(centerY); }
715
716 QRectF rect() const { return path().boundingRect(); }
717 void setRect(const QRectF& r) { QPainterPath p; p.addRect(r); setPath(p); }
718 void setRect(EmbReal x, EmbReal y, EmbReal w, EmbReal h) { QPainterPath p; p.addRect(x,y,w,h); setPath(p); }
719 QLineF line() const { return objLine; }
720 void setLine(const QLineF& li) { QPainterPath p; p.moveTo(li.p1()); p.lineTo(li.p2()); setPath(p); objLine = li; }
721 void setLine(EmbReal x1, EmbReal y1, EmbReal x2, EmbReal y2) { QPainterPath p; p.moveTo(x1,y1); p.lineTo(x2,y2); setPath(p); objLine.setLine(x1,y1,x2,y2); }
722
723 void setObjectColor(const QColor& color);
724 void setObjectColorRGB(QRgb rgb);
725 void setObjectLineType(Qt::PenStyle lineType);
726 void setObjectLineWeight(EmbReal lineWeight);
727 void setObjectPath(const QPainterPath& p) { setPath(p); }
728 void setObjectRubberMode(int mode) { objRubberMode = mode; }
729 void setObjectRubberPoint(const QString& key, const QPointF& point) { objRubberPoints.insert(key, point); }
730 void setObjectRubberText(const QString& key, const QString& txt) { objRubberTexts.insert(key, txt); }
731
732 virtual QRectF boundingRect() const;
733 virtual QPainterPath shape() const { return path(); }
734
735 void drawRubberLine(const QLineF& rubLine, QPainter* painter = 0, const char* colorFromScene = 0);
736
737 virtual void vulcanize() = 0;
738 virtual QPointF mouseSnapPoint(const QPointF& mousePoint) = 0;
739 virtual QList<QPointF> allGripPoints() = 0;
740 virtual void gripEdit(const QPointF& before, const QPointF& after) = 0;
741protected:
742 QPen lineWeightPen() const { return lwtPen; }
743 void realRender(QPainter* painter, const QPainterPath& renderPath);
744};
